 {"id":"franken_networkx-i87d","title":"parity: DiGraph and MultiDiGraph to_directed() should preserve NetworkX edge order","description":"Calling to_directed() on directed graph families should preserve their current edge iteration order under NetworkX, but FrankenNetworkX reorders edges. On a DiGraph with a->b, b->a, b->c, FrankenNetworkX yields [('b','a'), ('b','c'), ('a','b')] while NetworkX yields [('a','b'), ('b','a'), ('b','c')]. On a MultiDiGraph with a->b(k1), a->b(k2), b->a(k3), b->c(k4), FrankenNetworkX reorders both keys and edge groups. Match the upstream edge/key order contract for DiGraph.to_directed() and MultiDiGraph.to_directed().","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:17:56.225324376Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T08:17:56.225324376Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
